-- Help article HA-00049 — documents the Insert Signature Tab picker on
-- MergeFieldTextarea and the underlying anchor format the PDF renderer
-- scans for. Closes the documentation gap that explains why envelope_tabs
-- has been empty in production until this slice: authors had no UI
-- affordance to insert anchors, and the niche format was undocumented.
--
-- Companion to the frontend slice in the same commit:
--   src/components/RecordDetail.jsx — MergeFieldTextarea now exposes a
--   second toolbar button "Insert Signature Tab" beside the existing
--   "Insert Merge Field" button. Picker takes a recipient ordinal
--   (1-20) and a tab type (Signature / Initials / Date Signed / Text
--   Input) and inserts the corresponding anchor token at the cursor
--   in the exact format the renderer's regex expects:
--   /\\(sig|initial|date|text)(\d+)\\/g

with new_article as (
  insert into help_articles (
    ha_record_number, ha_slug, ha_title, ha_category, ha_summary, ha_body_markdown,
    ha_created_by, ha_updated_by, ha_is_deleted, ha_is_published
  ) values (
    '',
    'signature-tab-picker-and-anchor-format',
    'Signature tabs in document templates — placing signatures, initials, dates, and text inputs',
    'Communications',
    'Use the Insert Signature Tab button on the template body to drop a signature, initials, date, or text-input anchor at the cursor. The PDF renderer converts each anchor into a sized, recipient-bound tab on the unsigned PDF, which becomes a real envelope_tabs row when the envelope is sent.',
    E'### What this is\n\nWhen authoring a Document Template, the body editor (the **HTML / Markdown Body** field on a Document Template record) is a `MergeFieldTextarea`. It has two toolbar buttons:\n\n- **Insert Merge Field** — picks a `{{path.to.field}}` token from any related object\n- **Insert Signature Tab** — picks a signature/initials/date/text anchor for a specific recipient\n\nThis article covers the second button. For merge fields see HA-00042. For the envelope send flow see HA-00043.\n\n### Why this exists\n\nThe PDF renderer at `render-document-template-pdf` scans the rendered template body for anchor tokens. Each anchor becomes a **tab** — a sized rectangle on a specific page where the recipient signs, initials, dates, or types. When the envelope is sent, every detected anchor materializes as a row in `envelope_tabs` with `tab_x`, `tab_y`, `tab_width`, `tab_height`, `tab_page`, `tab_type`, and `recipient_id` already resolved. The recipient then sees those rectangles on the signing portal and fills them in.\n\nBefore this picker existed, the anchor format was undocumented and the only way to author tabs was to remember the exact niche syntax and type it manually. The picker eliminates that — pick recipient and tab type, click, anchor lands at the cursor.\n\n### The anchor format\n\nFour anchor types, each scoped to a recipient by ordinal:\n\n| Display name | Token format | Default size (points) | Typical use |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| Signature | `\\sig<n>\\` | 180 × 36 | Full signature line |\n| Initials | `\\initial<n>\\` | 60 × 30 | Initial-each-paragraph or initial-acknowledgment |\n| Date Signed | `\\date<n>\\` | 90 × 18 | Auto-populates on sign |\n| Text Input | `\\text<n>\\` | 140 × 18 | Free-text field — comments, full legal name, etc. |\n\nThe `<n>` is the **recipient order** — 1 is the primary signer, 2 is the second recipient in the routing order, and so on. Most templates use ordinal 1 because most envelopes have a single recipient. Multi-recipient templates use ascending ordinals to bind anchors to specific signers.\n\nExample template body with all four types for a single signer:\n\n```\n<p>By signing below, I acknowledge that project {{project.name}} is complete.</p>\n<p>Signature: \\sig1\\ </p>\n<p>Initials: \\initial1\\ &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Date: \\date1\\ </p>\n<p>Additional comments: \\text1\\ </p>\n```\n\nThe scanner uses this regex: `/\\\\(sig|initial|date|text)(\\d+)\\\\/g`. Backslashes are literal. Anchors must appear in the body exactly as the picker emits them — including the surrounding spaces, which keep the anchor measured as its own inline run rather than concatenated with adjacent words.\n\n### Recipient ordinal binding\n\nWhen an envelope is sent, the recipients list submitted by the sender (via `SendForSignatureModal`) is assigned `recipient_order` values 1, 2, 3, … in the order presented. The renderer matches each anchor''s `<n>` against that order. An anchor with no matching recipient is dropped during send — the envelope still goes out, but the dropped anchors are recorded in the `envelope_events` audit trail under event type `Created` with key `dropped_anchors`.\n\nThis means: if a template has `\\sig2\\` but the sender only added one recipient, that anchor is silently ignored. Templates should be authored to match the recipient pattern they''re intended for — single-signer templates use `<n>=1` exclusively, two-party agreements use `1` for the first party and `2` for the second.\n\n### Using the picker\n\n1. Open a Document Template record (Admin → Document Templates → click a row)\n2. The template must be in **Draft** status — Active templates are locked against edits by the `prevent_active_document_template_edits` trigger\n3. Click into the **HTML / Markdown Body** field to enter edit mode\n4. Position the cursor where the anchor should appear in the rendered PDF\n5. Click **Insert Signature Tab**\n6. Set the recipient ordinal (defaults to 1) and click the desired tab type\n7. The anchor inserts at the cursor with a leading and trailing space\n\nThe picker remembers the last ordinal used during the session so consecutive inserts for the same signer don''t require re-typing the number.\n\n### Geometry and sizing\n\nDefault sizes (in PDF points; 72 points = 1 inch) are baked into the renderer:\n\n- Signature: 180 wide × 36 tall — fits a typical handwritten signature scan\n- Initials: 60 × 30 — narrower, similar height to allow initialing in tight columns\n- Date Signed: 90 × 18 — fits `MM/DD/YYYY` in 12-point text\n- Text Input: 140 × 18 — single-line free text\n\nIf the anchor falls near a page break, the renderer keeps it on the page that contains its surrounding text. Anchors are never split across pages. If you need a signature block in a specific page position, surround it with paragraph breaks rather than relying on inline placement.\n\n### Verifying placement before publishing\n\nThe template must be **Active** to send a real envelope, but `render-document-template-pdf` accepts `preview: true` which bypasses the Active gate. The Document Template detail page has a Preview action that exercises this — generates a PDF with all merge fields resolved against a sample parent record and all anchors rendered as visible boxes for visual verification. Use Preview before publishing to confirm anchor positions look right.\n\n### When envelope_tabs rows appear\n\nThe sequence:\n\n1. Author drops anchors using the picker on a Draft template\n2. Author publishes the template to Active\n3. Sender opens any record matching the template''s `related_object` (e.g. a Project for the Project Completion Acknowledgment template)\n4. Sender clicks **Send for Signature** on the record\n5. `send-envelope` calls `render-document-template-pdf` against the published snapshot\n6. The renderer scans the rendered body, emits one anchor result per match\n7. `send-envelope` inserts one `envelope_tabs` row per anchor, with geometry, recipient_id (resolved via ordinal), and tab_type\n8. The unsigned PDF is stored at `signatures/envelopes/<envelope_id>/unsigned.pdf`\n9. The first recipient gets a signing link\n10. They see each tab as an overlay on the PDF in the signing portal\n\nDropped anchors (anchor ordinal exceeds recipient count) are silently skipped at step 7 and logged in the Created envelope_event metadata.\n\n### Common authoring mistakes\n\n- **Forgetting the trailing backslash**: `\\sig1` (no closing `\\`) is not matched by the regex and renders as literal text. The picker always emits both backslashes; if you''re hand-typing, double-check both are present.\n- **Using curly braces**: `{{sig1}}` is merge-field syntax, not anchor syntax. Anchors only match the backslash-delimited format.\n- **Anchor in an Active template**: edits are blocked by the `prevent_active_document_template_edits` trigger. Unpublish to Draft, edit, re-publish to Active.\n- **Mismatched ordinals across recipients**: if the template has `\\sig1\\` and `\\sig3\\` but the sender adds two recipients, the `\\sig3\\` anchor is dropped silently. Use contiguous ordinals starting at 1.\n- **Anchor inside an HTML attribute**: `<a href="\\sig1\\">click</a>` will not be detected — the renderer parses HTML first and the anchor must appear in the text content, not inside a tag attribute.\n\n### Related\n\n- HA-00042 — Document and email templates (authoring, publishing, merge fields)\n- HA-00043 — Envelopes and e-signature (send flow, signing portal, voiding, audit trail)\n- Renderer source: edge function `render-document-template-pdf` (`htmlToPdf.ts`)\n- Picker source: `MergeFieldTextarea` in `src/components/RecordDetail.jsx`',
    'c5a01ec8-960f-42ab-8a9e-a49822de89af',
    'c5a01ec8-960f-42ab-8a9e-a49822de89af',
    false,
    true
  )
  returning id, ha_record_number
)
insert into help_article_anchors (
  haa_article_id, haa_anchor_type, haa_route, haa_object, haa_field, haa_concept, haa_sort_order
)
select id, anchor_type, route, object, field, concept, sort_order
from new_article, (values
  ('field'::text,   null::text,                       'document_templates'::text, 'body_html'::text,           null::text,                          10),
  ('field',         null,                              'document_templates',       'dt_authoring_mode',          null,                                11),
  ('concept',       null,                              null,                       null,                         'signature-tab-picker',              20),
  ('concept',       null,                              null,                       null,                         'signature-anchor-format',           21),
  ('concept',       null,                              null,                       null,                         'envelope-tabs',                     22),
  ('concept',       null,                              null,                       null,                         'recipient-ordinal-binding',         23),
  ('concept',       null,                              null,                       null,                         'dropped-anchors',                   24),
  ('object',        null,                              'envelope_tabs',            null,                         null,                                30),
  ('object',        null,                              'document_templates',       null,                         null,                                31)
) as t(anchor_type, route, object, field, concept, sort_order);
